President Donald J. Trump convened two bipartisan dialogues with Members of the Opening Up America Again Congressional Group to discuss the next chapter of the COVID-19 recovery. He also celebrated the vital role truckers play in keeping America well-stocked. Later, he discussed his health-based vision for putting the nation back to work with America's Governors. In the evening, President Trump presented his guidelines on the three phases of Opening Up America Again at a press conference. He remains committed to taking decisive actions to keep the nation healthy and prosperous. More information about the guidelines can be found at WhiteHouse.gov/OpeningAmerica.